WEBVTT

00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:31.816
at the dose and frequency
that worked for her.

00:04:31.840 --> 00:04:35.216
And if it didn't work for her,
then she could make changes.

00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:36.656
Everything was up to her.

00:04:36.680 --> 00:04:38.376
The most important thing she said

00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:41.056
was she didn't need
anybody else's permission --

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:43.696
not a clinic appointment,
not a doctor's prescription,

00:04:43.720 --> 00:04:45.256
not a pharmacist's order.

00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:47.176
It was all up to her.

00:04:47.200 --> 00:04:49.000
She was in control.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:53.216
And if that seems like a little thing
for somebody with chronic illness,

00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:54.440
it's not -- not at all.

00:04:55.280 --> 00:04:57.456
When we face a chronic serious illness,

00:04:57.480 --> 00:05:02.776
whether it's rheumatoid arthritis
or lupus or cancer or diabetes,